description: A rocket that struck a soccer field killed at least 12 children and teenagers in Israeli territory in the Golan Heights. Israel blames the Iranian-backed militant group Hezbollah for what it says is the largest attack against its civilians since October 7. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez reports.
title: Rocket strike in Israeli territory kills at least 12, including children, Israel blames Hezbollah

description: In a defining moment from the Tokyo Olympics, Simone Biles pulled out of the competition after a scary run-in with what gymnasts call the “twisties.” Since then, she’s prioritized her mental health and now goes to therapy every week. Biles tells NBC News’ Hoda Kotb that three years later, she’s looking for redemption in Paris.
title: Simone Biles prepares for Olympics comeback

description: A dominating race in the men’s 4x100m freestyle relay secured Team USA its first gold medal of the Paris Olympics. Katie Ledecky also won her first medal of the games. It was a wet start for athletes outside the pool too, with downpours drenching the beach volleyball and cycling tournaments, and raising questions about the cleanliness of the Seine for future competitions. NBC News’ Stephanie Gosk reports.
title: Team USA wins gold on Day 1 of Paris Olympics

description: PARIS — The extravagant opening ceremony of the 2024 Paris Olympics has caused fury among the populist and religious right in the United States and elsewhere, with critics especially unhappy about an apparent depiction of the Last Supper featuring drag performers.
title: Drag performance resembling Last Supper at Olympic opening ceremony rankles conservatives

description: A rocket attack Saturday on a soccer field in the Israeli-controlled Golan Heights killed at least 10 people and wounded several others, including children, hours after an Israeli airstrike on south Lebanon killed three members of the militant Hezbollah group.
title: Rocket attack on town in Israeli-controlled Golan Heights kills 10, rescue official says

description: USA lost to Cuba in beach volleyball at the 2024 Paris Olympics.
title: Beach volleyball begins under the Eiffel Tower despite the torrential rains

description: Israeli airstrikes hit a school being used by displaced people in central Gaza on Saturday, killing dozens of people, as the country’s negotiators prepared to meet international mediators to discuss a proposed cease-fire.
title: Israeli airstrike hits a school sheltering people in Gaza, killing at least 30

description: SAINT-DENIS, France — Kassidy Cook and Sarah Bacon won silver in the women’s 3-meter synchronized springboard event on Saturday, securing America’s first medal of the 2024 Paris Olympic Games.
title: Synchronized divers Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook serve up first U.S. medals

description: Venezuelans are getting ready to participate in what stands to be the most consequential presidential election the South American nation has seen in more than a decade.
title: Three things to know about Venezuela's presidential election

description: Venezuelan voters will decide on Sunday whether to re-elect President Nicolás Maduro, who has been in office for 11 years, or allow the opposition a chance to improve the country after an economic collapse caused millions to emigrate. NBC News' Guad Venegas has the latest as concerns for a free and fair election grow.
title: A pivotal election looms over Venezuela as fear for free and fair polls grows
